    narr:narration """This hub gathers per-document **audience-tailoring assessments** scored against the rubric. The dominant axis is *who the writing speaks to*. Several documents are read as [technically tailored](narr:Assess_Tailoring_cm) — code examples, type signatures, assumed domain knowledge — with [Git/RDF/SPARQL framings](narr:RubricAssess_Tailoring_1) and [developer-centric metaphors](narr:RubricAssess_tailoring) recurring. A parallel cluster scores *explicit multi-persona segmentation*: the [collective-memory doc spans coordinators, sales execs, educators](narr:Assess_Tailoring_collective_memory), one [codifies an 'audience segmentation' section](narr:RubricAssess_Tailoring), and the [Jan-7 assessment praises seven distinct role personas](narr:RubricAssess_Tailoring_20260107) as exceptional. A third strand reads enterprise/executive fit: the [the customer's chief architect pitch tailored to CFO/CTO/CEO](narr:Assessment_Tailoring_CustomerArchitect), [GTM champion profiles](narr:RubricAssess_Tailoring_GTM), and a [CEO/strategist audience shift](narr:Assessment_Tailoring_IPCrisis). Assessments range from \"exceptional\" down to \"implied but not segmented,\" most appending a concrete improvement.""" ;
